data.text: Should’ve never tried to sign up for a COVID vaccine while driving through New Mexico. They keep finding ways to contact me to try to get me vaccinated. I keep explaining I am just in Texas. At this point, they’re going to Twitter DM me or send a carrier pigeon my way.

Some will say the saddest thing to happen to New Mexico over last couple years is loss of businesses, some would say masks especially on the kids, some would say vaccine mandates. I say it's the multiple cultures steeped in resistance to tyranny just simply laying down
